definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
Italy/Italian/abbr. for 意大利[Yi4 da4 li4]

sentences.english: "Well, it isn't as interesting, " said Hurstwood.
sentences.chinese: “哎，也不如芝加哥有意思，”赫斯渥说。

sentences.english: The social effect of an evening of one-on-one theatre is interesting.
sentences.chinese: 这一夜一对一剧场的社会反响很有意思。

sentences.english: It was a very interesting project. I really enjoyed working on it.
sentences.chinese: 这个项目很有意思，我很喜欢干。

sentences.english: To learn about the Wolong Panda Reserve was really interesting.
sentences.chinese: 了解到卧龙熊猫保护区的情况真有意思。

sentences.english: “There’s no question that Dr. Kearns’ wiper circuit was interesting, ” Daykin says.
sentences.chinese: 毫无疑问，卡恩斯博士的雨刷电路是非常有意思的。

sentences.english: We got to train with Ole Gunnar Solskjaer and that was really fun and he was really friendly.
sentences.chinese: 我们在索尔斯克亚的指导下训练，这很有意思。

sentences.english: The professor is really hilarious and funny. He makes it very interesting.
sentences.chinese: 教授真的很搞笑很滑稽，他课讲很有意思。

sentences.english: because I put myself in a position to meet a lot more interesting people in LA.
sentences.chinese: 因为当时我想接触那些有意思的人。

sentences.english: Interesting is the letter writing that they had to do.
sentences.chinese: 最有意思的是书信写作。

sentences.english: The Chinese life is colorful with many interesting folkways.
sentences.chinese: 中国人的生活多姿多彩，有许多很有意思的民俗。

sentences.english: It's really interesting that palindromes can be read in both directions.
sentences.chinese: 回文诗顺着倒着都能念，真有意思。

sentences.english: Japanese antisemitism is a particularly interesting case.
sentences.chinese: 日本的反犹主义则是一个相当有意思的话题。

sentences.english: That was the conclusion of our interesting conversation.
sentences.chinese: 我们有意思的谈话就这样结束了。

sentences.english: Funny way to get to a wizards' school, the train. Magic carpets all got punctures, have they?
sentences.chinese: 坐火车去魔法学院真有意思，难道飞毯都穿洞了吗？

sentences.english: Interestingly, forex markets haven't followed equities into this risk-off mode.
sentences.chinese: 有意思的是，外汇市场并未跟随股市进入避险模式。

sentences.english: An interesting book I have read is "Totem of wolves ".
sentences.chinese: 我曾经读过的一本很有意思的书，名叫《狼图腾》。

definition: thought-provoking/worth thinking over/to provide food for thought
to be playful/to be fond of one's fun
to be amazed/to be surprised/to wonder
erhua variant of 好玩[hao3 wan2]
to appear to be/to seem as if
